    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SPICER 13-INCH (310 MM) AND 14-INCH (350 MM) ANGLE-RING
        SINGLE PLATE PUSH-TYPE CLUTCH - CLUTCH ADJUSTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CLUTCH ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <para>Adjust the clutch for 1-1/2 inch (38.1 mm) free pedal. Refer to Group 11 - CLUTCH LINKAGE.</para>
        <para>If the clutch is properly adjusted with 1-1/2 inch (38.1 mm) free pedal obtained, the following dimensions
            will apply for clutch disengagement:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release bearing-to-lever clearance: 1/8 inch (3.14 mm)</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Normal release bearing travel to disengage: 1/2 inch (12.7 mm)</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Total release yoke travel required: 5/8 inch (15.7 mm).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
